  "text": "The search for biomaterials that are able to provide for the optimal resistance to the infection can be based only on the deep understanding of the interactions between bacteria and biomaterials' [CITATION_1] . The adhesion in the combined cultivation of Staphylococcus aureus and the Lactobacillus plantarum Ts probiotic bacterium on the surface of different metals is investigated [CITATION_2] . Also, the biofilm in vitro in the combined cultivation of Staphylococcus aureus and the Lactobacillus plantarum probiotic bacterium on the surface of different metal materials for fixed dental prostheses (Magnum Splendidum; Magnum Ni-Cr-Fe, Ruby Alloy-P, Ruby Alloy-C, and Ruby Alloy) is investigated [unpublished results].",
